<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-07-03T06:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-07-03T06:00:00-05:00" n="592" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d592">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">560.M2/359: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Berne</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-07-03T12:00:00+01:00">July 3,
                                1933—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received July 4—6:34 a.m.]</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>22. Department’s telegram No. 30, June 28, 7 p.m.<note n="6" xml:id="d592fn6">See telegram No. 73, June 27, 11 a.m., to the Chairman of the American
                            delegation, <ref target="#pg_785">p. 785</ref>.</note> League in
                        acknowledgment asks whether withdrawal applies also to supplementary
                        agreement to convention and protocol signed July 11, 1928. Please
                        instruct.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>